By now, once you create a rule which scope is restricted to one project and add a _Clone Issue_ or _Create Issue_ action, when you try to set the _Components_ field for the issue to be created, the drop-down menu only offers the _Components_ values related to the original project.

If we set the scope to multi-projects instead, the drop-down menu lists _Components_ field options related to all projects in the instance, what might also be confusing.
{panel}
*It would be good if the drop-down menu only select options from the destination project.*
{panel}

h3. Issue Summary

Cannot create a project link between two Jira sites. These projects are Classic and have a product link created and working. When trying to create a project link nothing happens by clicking on the "Add Link" button and choosing Jira from the Jira product link listed.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Testing from two Jira sites that have Product app-link created;
 # In one of the sites, open a classic software project, go to Project settings > Summary > Application Links: Configure Project Links;
 # Click on the "Add Link" button and choose Jira from the Jira product link listed;
 # Nothing happens on the user interface;
 # This was reproducible on my test site;
 # A video is attached to better show the results;

h3. Expected Results

A link should be created between Jira projects to share information between these two projects. 
h3. Actual Results

Nothing happens on UI, but when checking Developer's tools > Network I see the following message when trying to create a project link(Project settings > Summary > Application Links:
Configure Project Links).
{noformat}
{code: "CREDENTIALS_REQUIRED",…}code: "CREDENTIALS_REQUIRED"url: "https://rgtn.atlassian.net/plugins/servlet/applinks/oauth/login-dance/authorize?applicationLinkID=7fd4ea7c-ffa1-31be-9a75-b924c0dc4a6f"{noformat}
The only documentation I found in regard to this was for server.
[https://confluence.atlassian.com/applinks/configuring-project-links-across-applications-976158802.html]
h3. Workaround

No workaround was found.

h3. Issue Summary

When attempting to update an issue with a description that contains an empty `bulletList`, a 400 response code is returned, as well as the following message:
 {
 "errorMessages": [
 "We couldn't save your changes. Copy your content, then try reloading the page."
 ],
 "errors": {}
 }
 This message is not descriptive enough to help pinpoint the issue, and would be more beneficial if it contained details about what caused the error,
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Call /rest/api/3/issue/\{issueOrKey} with description containing empty `bulletList`

{code:java}
{    "fields": {        
        "description": {            
             "version": 1,            
             "type": "doc",            
             "content": [{                
                "type": "bulletList",                
                "content": [{                    
                   "type": "listItem"                
                }]            
             }]        
        }    
     }
}
{code}

h3. Expected Results

A 400 response code with the an error message containing details about what caused the failure
h3. Actual Results

{
 "errorMessages": [
 "We couldn't save your changes. Copy your content, then try reloading the page."
 ],
 "errors": {}
 }
h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

Today, when you filter to return issues on a specific Sprint, it also returns all the issues which were added to previous nested Sprints before:

{{Sprint = Sprint 1}}

We should have a way to search for issues firstly added to that specific Sprint, with no previous Sprints nested to it. You can filter by closedSprints() if the sprint in the JQL is currently active, however, if the current search Sprint is also closed, it will not work.
